# OneKeyRestore

To restore a volume, you need a computer as well as a OneKeyRestore USB key or its ISO on any bootable media.

#### _To launch a volume restore_

1. Boot on the OneKeyRestore key\(or the ISO\).

![](../.gitbook/assets/onekey-intro.PNG)

2. Select the keyboard layout.

![](../.gitbook/assets/onekey-keyboard-1.PNG)

3. Enter the backup box \(server\) IP address.

![](../.gitbook/assets/onekey-ip-3.PNG)

4. Enter its login and password.

![](../.gitbook/assets/onekey-login-4.PNG)

![](../.gitbook/assets/onekey-mdp-5.PNG)

5. Select the workstation you want to restore.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

6. Select the disk you want to restore.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

7. Select the version of each partition you want to restore, by default this is the last.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

8. Select the target.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

9. Confirm.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

The restore is processing.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

{% hint style="info" %}
If you want to backup the restored workstation, you need to reinstall the agent.
{% endhint %}
